All I know is where I get it!

65
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,880 
Freeze.

66
00:10:41,040 --> 00:10:43,920 
Nobody move. This is a bust.

67
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:05,840 
Ladies, stay down.

68
00:12:09,720 --> 00:12:12,800 
Somebody! Open the fridge, damn it!

69
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:16,200 
Come on!

70
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:42,280 
Can't shoot a kid, can you, fucker?

71
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,240 
{y:i}Can't shoot a kid...

72
00:12:54,560 --> 00:12:56,560 
{y:i}Throw it home, Dad!

73
00:13:07,480 --> 00:13:08,960 
Shut up!

74
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:14,400 
Drop it or the little shit's dead!
I'll blow its fucking head off, man!

75
00:13:14,640 --> 00:13:16,240 
Lewis...

76
00:13:16,480 --> 00:13:18,240 
...hang it up.

77
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:27,760 
Now, no shit from either one of you!

78
00:13:27,960 --> 00:13:29,960 
- And don't try to follow me!
- We won't.

79
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:31,640 
The baby's going with me!

80
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:34,640 
I'll kill it, man. I'll do it. I'll fucking kill it!

81
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:37,080 
We can't have that.

82
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:51,840 
Nice shooting.

83
00:13:55,280 --> 00:13:56,880 
See you, Jimmy.

84
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:15,160 
- Hi, Mom.
- Hi.

85
00:14:50,400 --> 00:14:54,080 
Don't do it! No! Stop... Stop it, Alex!

86
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:21,360 
{y:i}OCP defines you as a machine...

87
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:26,840 
...that utilizes some living tissue.
You understand that.

88
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:28,920 
Yes.

89
00:15:29,920 --> 00:15:34,440 
And so do you
consider yourself human?

90
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:38,600 
I require an answer.

91
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:42,320 
Stop tape.

92
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:47,440 
You have any idea what you're doing
to that poor woman?

93
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:50,480 
Take a look at her file.

94
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:52,080 
Go on.

95
00:15:52,440 --> 00:15:57,240 
Officer, Mrs. Murphy
is bringing suit against OCP.

96
00:15:57,480 --> 00:16:00,040 
My name is Tom Delaney.
I'm representing her.

97
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:03,440 
Up to a few months ago,
she wouldn't leave her bedroom.

98
00:16:03,640 --> 00:16:06,440 
Then there were hypnotists
and harmonic treatments.

99
00:16:06,640 --> 00:16:10,560 
Then you pull this shit!
Driving past her house day after day.

100
00:16:10,760 --> 00:16:14,240 
Spying on her. Trying to make her
think her husband is still alive.

101
00:16:14,480 --> 00:16:17,240 
She's barely started
to accept the loss.

102
00:16:17,520 --> 00:16:20,720 
- You're ripping her to pieces.
- And for what?

103
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:24,160 
Do you think you could ever be
a husband to her?

104
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:27,960 
I mean, what can you offer her?

105
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:30,160 
Companionship?

106
00:16:32,280 --> 00:16:33,600 
Love?

107
00:16:34,760 --> 00:16:36,720 
A man's love?

108
00:16:52,480 --> 00:16:53,760 
No.

109
00:16:55,560 --> 00:16:57,120 
Roll tape.

110
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:03,760 
Are you Alex Murphy?

111
00:17:06,360 --> 00:17:07,760 
No.

112
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:09,280 
Are you human?

113
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:11,960 
No.

114
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:14,720 
You are simply a machine.

115
00:17:16,280 --> 00:17:18,120 
I am...

116
00:17:18,880 --> 00:17:20,360 
...a machine.

117
00:17:20,720 --> 00:17:22,400 
Nothing more.

118
00:17:23,040 --> 00:17:24,840 
Nothing more.

119
00:17:28,640 --> 00:17:30,560 
That'll do it. Stop tape.

120
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:37,520 
Now, you stay there.
All right, go get her.

121
00:17:37,720 --> 00:17:40,840 
Let's be decent about this.
Give them some privacy.

122
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:43,880 
I don't have a problem with that.

123
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:39,680 
Alex?

124
00:18:40,080 --> 00:18:42,040 
Don't you know me?

125
00:18:45,760 --> 00:18:47,760 
Don't you remember me?

126
00:18:50,280 --> 00:18:53,400 
Alex, it doesn't matter
what they've done to you...

127
00:18:54,920 --> 00:18:56,560 
Touch me.

128
00:19:06,240 --> 00:19:07,440 
It's cold.

129
00:19:08,160 --> 00:19:10,280 
They made this...

130
00:19:10,480 --> 00:19:12,240 
...to honor him.

131
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:19,840 
- No, l...
- Your husband is dead.

132
00:19:22,560 --> 00:19:24,080 
I don't know you.

133
00:19:51,520 --> 00:19:53,480 
Why is this happening?

134
00:20:10,040 --> 00:20:13,480 
I thought all communication systems
were the same.

135
00:20:13,920 --> 00:20:16,800 
I tried to save the company
a few bucks.

136
00:20:17,360 --> 00:20:21,520 
It took two days to download specs
from Cleveland.

137
00:20:23,360 --> 00:20:25,280 
I lost the account.

138
00:20:49,320 --> 00:20:52,360 
It hardly befits my dignity
to have to come to you, Johnson.

139
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:55,200 
Sorry for the slight inconvenience,
Your Honor.

140
00:20:55,440 --> 00:20:57,640 
Twenty minutes in rush hour isn't slight.

141
00:20:57,840 --> 00:20:59,840 
Not when you're mayor of a major city!

142
00:21:00,040 --> 00:21:03,640 
When will you start paying the cops
so they'll go back to work?

143
00:21:03,840 --> 00:21:05,560 
We're not a charity.

144
00:21:05,760 --> 00:21:07,960 
The city owes us over $37 million.

145
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:11,640 
- You'll have to cut us some slack.
- A deadline's a deadline. Sorry.

146
00:21:11,840 --> 00:21:14,280 
How are we supposed to raise
that kind of money?

147
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:16,160 
You aren't.

148
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:20,280 
- What the hell is he talking about?
- We don't expect you to pay.

149
00:21:20,440 --> 00:21:22,680 
Let me refer you to our contract.

150
00:21:24,560 --> 00:21:26,040 
"In the event of default...

151
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:30,920 
...OCP shall have the uncontested right
of foreclosure on all city assets."

152
00:21:33,440 --> 00:21:34,960 
You signed this.

153
00:21:35,320 --> 00:21:37,920 
We miss one payment,
and you can foreclose?

154
00:21:38,120 --> 00:21:39,920 
We can and we will.

155
00:21:40,320 --> 00:21:42,480 
We're taking Detroit private.

156
00:21:42,760 --> 00:21:45,240 
So you deliberately undermined
our credit.

157
00:21:45,480 --> 00:21:47,600 
That was the easy part.

158
00:21:48,520 --> 00:21:50,920 
And you engineered the police strike.

159
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:53,320 
You want Detroit to tear itself apart...

160
00:21:53,480 --> 00:21:56,480 
...so you can raid it like you would
any other corporation!

161
00:21:56,640 --> 00:21:58,680 
Do you know how many people
are dying?

162
00:21:58,920 --> 00:22:00,120 
You're murderers!

163
00:22:00,320 --> 00:22:03,200 
I'd advise you to say nothing further.
It might be...

164
00:22:03,360 --> 00:22:04,600 
...actionable.

165
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:06,360 
It's bullshit!

166
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:09,720 
- Bullshit, you senile, old bastard!
- All right, calm down.

167
00:22:09,880 --> 00:22:11,960 
- We better get out of here.
- I'm okay!

168
00:22:12,160 --> 00:22:14,200 
- Calm down. We better leave.
- I'm calm.

169
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:16,520 
- Calm down. Easy.
- I'm okay.

170
00:22:16,720 --> 00:22:18,000 
All right, good.

171
00:22:18,160 --> 00:22:21,160 
- I'm in control. Everything is fine. It's okay.
- Relax.

172
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:23,320 
I'm fine.

173
00:22:23,520 --> 00:22:25,440 
One last thing, gentlemen.

174
00:22:25,640 --> 00:22:27,280 
We will sue your asses.

175
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:29,320 
Give it your best shot.

176
00:22:29,520 --> 00:22:33,200 
Fuck you, you old, senile bastard!
This is bullshit!

177
00:22:33,400 --> 00:22:35,000 
Fuck you!

178
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:37,680 
- This is bullshit!
- Calm down.

179
00:22:41,680 --> 00:22:45,480 
I've been very patient, Johnson.
Five months.

180
00:22:46,480 --> 00:22:48,440 
- Who's that?
- That's Dr. Juliette Faxx.

181
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:51,160 
Just moved up to head the
Attitude Adjustment team.

182
00:22:51,360 --> 00:22:55,280 
Five months. Ninety million dollars!

183
00:22:57,200 --> 00:23:01,160 
- I want to see some results.
- Yes, sir. I'll show you what we have.

184
00:23:02,960 --> 00:23:05,600 
{y:i}OCP pioneered cyborg technology.

185
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:08,440 
{y:i}And now we take
{y:i}a quantum leap forward.

186
00:23:08,640 --> 00:23:10,840 
{y:i}State-of-the-art
{y:i}destructive capabilities...

187
00:23:11,040 --> 00:23:15,760 
{y:i}... commanded by a unique combination
{y:i}of software and organic systems.

188
00:23:15,920 --> 00:23:18,360 
{y:i}In every way,
{y:i}an improvement over the original.

189
00:23:18,760 --> 00:23:23,080 
{y:i}It gives me great pleasure
{y:i}to introduce to you, Robocop 2.

190
00:23:34,040 --> 00:23:36,840 
{y:i}You are under arrest.

191
00:23:38,400 --> 00:23:40,600 
{y:i}Stop or I'll shoot.

192
00:23:41,680 --> 00:23:44,240 
{y:i}Stop or I'll shoot.

193
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:57,200 
{y:i}OCP is proud to present the future
{y:i}of urban pacification:

194
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:59,040 
{y:i}Robocop 2.

195
00:24:17,560 --> 00:24:19,760 
Ninety million.

196
00:24:22,160 --> 00:24:24,040 
They all go crazy.

197
00:24:24,240 --> 00:24:26,600 
Robots with emotional problems.

198
00:24:26,800 --> 00:24:29,200 
No, sir, not robots, cyborgs.

199
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:33,640 
Cybernetic organisms. We use living human
tissue and that's our whole problem.

200
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:36,880 
The candidates were all fine men,
respected police officers.

201
00:24:37,080 --> 00:24:39,040 
I reviewed their files myself.

202
00:24:39,240 --> 00:24:43,640 
Sir, police officers may not be
the best candidates for our purposes.

203
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:46,440 
They're a physical bunch.
They're macho, body-proud.

204
00:24:46,600 --> 00:24:50,080 
Stripped of all that it's no wonder
they become suicidal.

205
00:24:50,280 --> 00:24:52,440 
Our one success was a cop.

206
00:24:52,640 --> 00:24:55,080 
Well, yes, Mr. Johnson. Alex Murphy.

207
00:24:55,280 --> 00:24:58,200 
Top of his class,
devout Irish Catholic, family man.

208
00:24:58,400 --> 00:25:01,560 
Everything in his profile
indicates a fierce sense of duty.

209
00:25:01,720 --> 00:25:03,560 
That's probably what kept him alive.

210
00:25:03,720 --> 00:25:07,480 
With due respect, Dr. Faxx,
your area of expertise is psychology.

211
00:25:07,680 --> 00:25:08,960 
Not robotics.

212
00:25:09,160 --> 00:25:12,280 
There's no harm in hearing
the young lady out, is there?

213
00:25:12,440 --> 00:25:13,640 
No, sir.

214
00:25:13,840 --> 00:25:17,760 
Thank you, sir. I believe that Murphy's case
was unusual but not unique.

215
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:22,440 
We can find someone else, someone
to whom the prospect might even be...

216
00:25:22,640 --> 00:25:24,000 
...desirable.

217
00:25:25,520 --> 00:25:28,320 
I've never met anyone who wanted
to be a robot.

218
00:25:28,640 --> 00:25:32,440 
It would require a screening process,
one I'd would be happy to supervise.

219
00:25:32,640 --> 00:25:34,280 
The cost would be negligible.

220
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:38,960 
It would be a shame
to waste all the work that's been done.

221
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:40,960 
It certainly would.

222
00:25:41,160 --> 00:25:43,120 
Go to it. Report to me directly.

223
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:45,840 
Yes, sir.

224
00:25:46,880 --> 00:25:49,760 
You could learn a thing or two
from that girl, Johnson.

225
00:25:54,480 --> 00:25:56,440 
- Not for me!

226
00:25:56,640 --> 00:26:00,680 
Decent pay to decent cops!

227
00:26:05,240 --> 00:26:08,880 
Union's got a list!
We ain't forgetting who you are!

228
00:26:09,080 --> 00:26:10,520 
One at a time!

229
00:26:13,680 --> 00:26:16,360 
Please, one at a time.

230
00:26:19,840 --> 00:26:22,400 
Don't you know
what's going on out here?

231
00:26:24,960 --> 00:26:26,320 
It's the best we can do!

232
00:26:27,080 --> 00:26:29,800 
Hello, ladies!

233
00:26:34,480 --> 00:26:36,800 
They won't be fucking
with any more cops!

234
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:39,520 
They won't be fucking
with nobody, man!

235
00:27:16,920 --> 00:27:20,000 
Hob. That's him.

236
00:27:22,320 --> 00:27:23,800 
Thank you.

237
00:27:27,840 --> 00:27:29,400 
Nuke me!

238
00:27:33,360 --> 00:27:35,320 
Go ahead. Take two.

239
00:27:36,320 --> 00:27:38,360 
There's plenty of Nuke to go around.

240
00:27:40,120 --> 00:27:41,640 
I've lost him.

241
00:27:41,840 --> 00:27:43,600 
You haven't been around in a while.

242
00:27:43,760 --> 00:27:45,920 
Go ahead. This one's on me.

243
00:27:46,120 --> 00:27:48,440 
Five degrees south-southwest.

244
00:27:49,040 --> 00:27:50,840 
There's the little darling.

245
00:27:51,160 --> 00:27:52,440 
Good eyes, Murphy.

246
00:27:52,640 --> 00:27:54,680 
Good as money can buy.

247
00:27:54,880 --> 00:27:56,600 
Ferdy, you got out.

248
00:27:57,160 --> 00:27:59,120 
Well, I'll tell Cain, okay?

249
00:28:09,280 --> 00:28:12,000 
Better have something
to give me this time, officer.

250
00:28:14,680 --> 00:28:18,360 
One cop per car.
Okay, these are the routes.

251
00:28:19,040 --> 00:28:21,040 
Three cars.

252
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:23,000 
- One cop per car?
- That's right.

253
00:28:23,200 --> 00:28:27,440 
Sitting ducks. We set up three
snipers and that's all it takes.

254
00:28:28,880 --> 00:28:31,360 
- Pay the man.
- All right.

255
00:28:31,560 --> 00:28:32,800 
Thank you.

256
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:35,080 
- You didn't count it.
- That's all right.

257
00:28:35,280 --> 00:28:37,320 
You should really count it, you know.

258
00:28:37,520 --> 00:28:38,840 
It's okay.

259
00:28:39,040 --> 00:28:42,040 
Give him something
to help him with his conscience.

260
00:28:45,320 --> 00:28:47,640 
No, that's all right. I don't really want it.

261
00:28:47,840 --> 00:28:50,160 
Come on, Duffy. I know you need it.

262
00:29:09,400 --> 00:29:11,560 
Isn't this a school day?

263
00:29:16,680 --> 00:29:18,320 
Cops!

264
00:29:21,040 --> 00:29:22,560 
Oh, shit!

265
00:29:30,760 --> 00:29:31,760 
Oh, no.

266
00:29:50,320 --> 00:29:51,800 
Freeze!

267
00:29:52,560 --> 00:29:55,040 
Turn around. Put your hands up.

268
00:30:10,720 --> 00:30:11,720 
Shit.

269
00:30:26,120 --> 00:30:28,800 
Officer Duffy, have a seat.

270
00:30:35,120 --> 00:30:37,760 
You look a little out of breath, bitch.

271
00:30:40,680 --> 00:30:45,640 
- You sold us out, Officer Duffy.
- What are you talking about, Murph?

272
00:30:45,840 --> 00:30:48,520 
Where is Cain?

273
00:30:48,680 --> 00:30:51,360 
I don't know any Cain.

274
00:30:53,520 --> 00:30:55,600 
Where is Cain?

275
00:30:55,800 --> 00:30:58,160 
I don't know.

276
00:31:05,200 --> 00:31:07,560 
Where is Cain?!

277
00:31:07,800 --> 00:31:10,200 
I told you, I don't know!

278
00:31:33,760 --> 00:31:35,760 
Where?

279
00:31:35,920 --> 00:31:38,480 
River Rouge. The old sludge plant.

280
00:31:39,760 --> 00:31:42,040 
You're a rotten cop.

281
00:34:34,360 --> 00:34:35,840 
Go.

282
00:35:47,520 --> 00:35:50,280 
- You.
- You want me?

283
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:52,120 
Dead or alive.

284
00:35:54,080 --> 00:35:55,320 
Then one of us must die.

285
00:35:56,240 --> 00:35:57,800 
Dead, then.

286
00:36:21,640 --> 00:36:23,400 
Jesus...

287
00:36:23,560 --> 00:36:25,600 
...had days like this.

288
00:36:26,840 --> 00:36:29,520 
Hounded and attacked like a criminal.

289
00:36:30,040 --> 00:36:32,960 
But like him, I don't blame you.

290
00:36:33,160 --> 00:36:35,680 
They program you, and you do it.

291
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:41,080 
- I will kill you.
- Oh, you just tried.

292
00:36:42,480 --> 00:36:43,960 
And...

293
00:36:44,160 --> 00:36:45,440 
...I forgive you.

294
00:37:58,160 --> 00:38:00,040 
Why'd you stop? You got it cracked.

295
00:38:00,200 --> 00:38:01,400 
I'm tired.

296
00:38:01,960 --> 00:38:04,400 
They say he's got a brain.
I want to see it.

297
00:38:10,240 --> 00:38:12,720 
You think it was me that beat you?

298
00:38:13,040 --> 00:38:14,880 
It wasn't.

299
00:38:15,480 --> 00:38:16,760 
It was this.

300
00:38:33,120 --> 00:38:34,880 
It's too tough.

301
00:38:35,360 --> 00:38:37,480 
Try here at the joint.

302
00:38:43,440 --> 00:38:44,640 
Yeah!

303
00:38:49,160 --> 00:38:50,800 
Look at that!

304
00:39:00,440 --> 00:39:02,520 
Come on. Cut it out.

305
00:39:05,400 --> 00:39:07,440 
How's it taste?

306
00:39:19,760 --> 00:39:21,200 
What the hell's going on?!

307
00:39:22,280 --> 00:39:24,280 
Man, just look at him.

308
00:39:26,360 --> 00:39:28,200 
Christ, he's been stripped.

309
00:39:41,120 --> 00:39:44,920 
Let's not get carried away here.
We're talking about a piece of equipment.

310
00:39:45,120 --> 00:39:47,360 
Don't tell me he can't suffer.

311
00:39:47,920 --> 00:39:49,640 
Just look at him.

312
00:39:50,160 --> 00:39:52,360 
It's electrical.

313
00:39:52,560 --> 00:39:54,240 
Bullshit.

314
00:39:54,600 --> 00:39:57,360 
I know every inch of him.
Every circuit.

315
00:39:57,560 --> 00:39:59,520 
Every living nerve.

316
00:39:59,720 --> 00:40:03,640 
His pain centers are alive.
They're lit up like Christmas trees.

317
00:40:03,880 --> 00:40:06,680 
The back-up generator's
just making him twitch.

318
00:40:06,920 --> 00:40:08,400 
He's suffering.

319
00:40:09,160 --> 00:40:10,480 
How long can he last?

320
00:40:10,720 --> 00:40:12,360 
No way of knowing.

321
00:40:12,880 --> 00:40:15,200 
Got him on minimal life support.

322
00:40:16,360 --> 00:40:19,400 
Keeping the brain going
with microshocks.

323
00:40:20,920 --> 00:40:25,240 
- It's damn tricky. He could go anytime.
- Move. Move!

324
00:40:26,920 --> 00:40:28,360 
What's happening in here?

325
00:40:28,560 --> 00:40:33,000 
OCP is happening. These bastards
won't lift a finger to help him.

326
00:40:33,240 --> 00:40:36,080 
This unit needs
millions of dollars in parts.

327
00:40:36,280 --> 00:40:40,240 
You can't expect authorization for that
kind of cash overnight. Be reasonable.

328
00:40:40,440 --> 00:40:42,200 
If you don't fix him, it's murder.

329
00:40:42,400 --> 00:40:45,200 
Settle down. I'm doing you
a favor by talking to you.

330
00:40:45,760 --> 00:40:48,960 
You son of a bitch. He's in hell.

331
00:40:52,280 --> 00:40:53,640 
Fix him!

332
00:40:55,080 --> 00:40:56,640 
We'll be in touch.

333
00:41:04,600 --> 00:41:06,920 
Oh, man, you guys are the greatest!

334
00:41:07,120 --> 00:41:09,080 
Did you see their faces?

335
00:41:09,320 --> 00:41:12,400 
"We're gonna throw away
the key, Duffy."

336
00:41:14,320 --> 00:41:16,600 
The cops didn't give you trouble,
did they?

337
00:41:16,800 --> 00:41:20,520 
The usual shit from Reed.
They'll never prove anything.

338
00:41:21,040 --> 00:41:22,280 
Hey, want some?

339
00:41:22,480 --> 00:41:25,880 
Hey, I'm a minor.
Don't want to break any laws.

340
00:41:26,960 --> 00:41:28,440 
Here, you take it.

341
00:41:28,640 --> 00:41:30,960 
God, I just love you guys!

342
00:41:35,680 --> 00:41:37,120 
What happened?

343
00:41:37,960 --> 00:41:39,360 
Hey, where we going?

344
00:41:40,040 --> 00:41:43,080 
Hey, come on, guys.
This isn't funny, man.

345
00:41:43,280 --> 00:41:44,960 
Oh, God, my head.

346
00:41:45,320 --> 00:41:48,360 
My head is killing me.

347
00:41:49,520 --> 00:41:51,320 
Hey, man. What's?

348
00:41:51,520 --> 00:41:54,920 
Hey, Cain! Hey, it's good to see you.

349
00:41:55,200 --> 00:41:56,720 
Thanks for getting me out.

350
00:41:58,480 --> 00:42:00,840 
- I can't get up.
- You noticed that one.

351
00:42:01,040 --> 00:42:04,560 
- Cain, I don't know what the kid told you...
- You told them, Duffy.

352
00:42:04,720 --> 00:42:07,080 
- You told them where we were.
- That's not true.

353
00:42:07,240 --> 00:42:12,000 
- We know all about it, Duffy.
- You think you're the only cop we have?

354
00:42:14,640 --> 00:42:16,240 
Oh, shit!

355
00:42:16,760 --> 00:42:19,080 
Cain. Cain, come on.
Man, I'm begging you, man!

356
00:42:19,240 --> 00:42:21,600 
Look, I'll do anything!

357
00:42:21,960 --> 00:42:24,760 
Okay. You're kidding, right?
Yeah, you're just kidding.

358
00:42:25,200 --> 00:42:29,000 
You scared me.
You taught me a lesson, man.

359
00:42:29,200 --> 00:42:32,440 
I'd never fuck with you,
because I really love you guys.

360
00:42:32,600 --> 00:42:34,600 
- I really do!
- Shut up!

361
00:42:34,800 --> 00:42:39,040 
I've been loyal. I know shit
that I still haven't even told you, Cain!

362
00:42:40,640 --> 00:42:43,560 
You deserve this, Duffy.
Cain might have been killed.

363
00:42:43,720 --> 00:42:45,080 
Okay. Okay.

364
00:42:45,360 --> 00:42:47,960 
Maybe you ought to have the kid leave.

365
00:42:48,800 --> 00:42:52,400 
- Why?
- What do you mean, "have the kid leave"?

366
00:42:53,240 --> 00:42:57,240 
That's a good touch. That's a good touch.
"Have the kid leave."

367
00:42:59,280 --> 00:43:01,920 
That's good. "Have the kid leave." Why?

368
00:43:03,560 --> 00:43:06,160 
Come on. It's over.

369
00:43:06,560 --> 00:43:09,760 
Come on, Cain! Come on, man.
What are you doing?

370
00:43:11,440 --> 00:43:12,960 
Come on!

371
00:43:27,840 --> 00:43:30,600 
You said you were
just gonna scare him!

372
00:43:30,800 --> 00:43:32,760 
Doesn't he look scared?

373
00:43:43,440 --> 00:43:45,240 
I can't believe you'd do this.

374
00:43:45,440 --> 00:43:48,400 
It hardly matters what you believe,
Mr. Schenk.

375
00:43:48,640 --> 00:43:51,400 
But these are criminals.
They're maniacs.

376
00:43:51,600 --> 00:43:54,600 
You're giving premature
value judgments.

377
00:43:55,960 --> 00:43:59,400 
All right, it may be true.
The subjects are socially misaligned.

378
00:43:59,600 --> 00:44:02,520 
Socially misaligned?
These are death row inmates!

379
00:44:02,680 --> 00:44:06,280 
And of no use to society. We need a
subject who'll welcome the power...

380
00:44:06,480 --> 00:44:08,320 
...the virtual immortality we offer.

381
00:44:08,520 --> 00:44:12,280 
Now, I really think this is a good place
to start looking.

382
00:44:14,000 --> 00:44:18,080 
- You're out of your mind.
- Is that your professional opinion?

383
00:44:18,760 --> 00:44:21,120 
Yes, goddamn it, it is! Yes!

384
00:44:21,320 --> 00:44:25,720 
And you are not using my lab to put
that kind of a brain into my cyborg.

385
00:44:25,880 --> 00:44:27,760 
We'd dearly miss you here.

386
00:44:29,920 --> 00:44:32,280 
You're the one that's gonna be
out of a job.

387
00:44:33,160 --> 00:44:35,840 
I'm going to take this directly
to Johnson.

388
00:44:37,040 --> 00:44:40,680 
He's just been waiting for an excuse
to get you fired.

389
00:44:48,920 --> 00:44:50,240 
Good morning, sir.

390
00:44:51,520 --> 00:44:53,760 
I'm sorry to bother you this early.

391
00:44:55,360 --> 00:44:56,640 
You seem agitated.

392
00:44:56,880 --> 00:44:59,080 
Frankly, I'm shocked.

393
00:44:59,560 --> 00:45:01,160 
Mr. Schenk just called.

394
00:45:01,360 --> 00:45:05,000 
Dr. Faxx has begun screening
candidates for the Robocop 2 project...

395
00:45:05,200 --> 00:45:08,840 
So I understand. It's very exciting.

396
00:45:09,080 --> 00:45:12,000 
She's screening psychotics, sir.
Murderers.

397
00:45:12,200 --> 00:45:15,080 
We aren't planning to build a toy,
Johnson.

398
00:45:15,240 --> 00:45:16,680 
Faxx knows what she's doing.

399
00:45:16,880 --> 00:45:20,640 
She's keeping Robocop offline.
It's a public-relations disaster.

400
00:45:21,240 --> 00:45:24,680 
You've got to learn to look
at the larger picture. The foreclosure.

401
00:45:24,880 --> 00:45:26,960 
You must know how important
that is to us.

402
00:45:27,160 --> 00:45:31,000 
With Robocop out of commission, the
chaos down there will increase...

403
00:45:31,240 --> 00:45:33,840 
...and the odds the city will fall
into our hands.

404
00:45:34,080 --> 00:45:38,640 
But a competent executive would find a way
to deal with the corporate image problem.

405
00:45:38,880 --> 00:45:41,400 
Couldn't agree with you more,
Mr. Johnson.

406
00:45:42,640 --> 00:45:44,640 
Fortunately, I have found a way.

407
00:45:44,840 --> 00:45:48,320 
Yes, Ms. Faxx and I have
already discussed it.

408
00:45:49,600 --> 00:45:53,200 
I know you'll help
to implement her ideas.

409
00:45:53,600 --> 00:45:55,240 
Of course, sir. Whatever I can do.

410
00:45:55,440 --> 00:45:56,680 
Anything else?

411
00:45:57,120 --> 00:45:59,920 
- Coffee?
- No, thank you.

412
00:46:00,160 --> 00:46:02,800 
Don't forget your shoes
on the way out.

413
00:46:35,960 --> 00:46:38,480 
He's my patient and critical.
I must stay with him.

414
00:46:38,640 --> 00:46:40,480 
We'll let you know when we need you.

415
00:46:40,640 --> 00:46:43,720 
Nobody on your staff has my experience
with him. You need me.

416
00:46:43,920 --> 00:46:45,400 
We don't need anybody.

417
00:46:45,600 --> 00:46:48,800 
"We." Who the hell are "we"?
You're a lawyer who knows nothing!

418
00:46:49,000 --> 00:46:51,720 
You're exactly this far
from getting fired, babe.

419
00:46:52,400 --> 00:46:54,120 
Shyster!

420
00:46:55,320 --> 00:46:56,960 
He's one of mine.

421
00:46:57,640 --> 00:46:59,640 
I want him back on his feet.

422
00:47:00,240 --> 00:47:03,440 
Maybe he will be,
or maybe we'll just sell the parts for scrap.

423
00:47:03,640 --> 00:47:05,320 
That's up to us.

424
00:47:05,480 --> 00:47:07,880 
You see, Robocop's off warranty.

425
00:47:11,680 --> 00:47:13,280 
Robocop's command program...

426
00:47:13,520 --> 00:47:16,840 
...his set of directives...

427
00:47:17,040 --> 00:47:21,320 
It determines his behavior.
It's time to update the program...

428
00:47:21,520 --> 00:47:25,120 
...and I would like to hear
from each one of you.

429
00:47:26,560 --> 00:47:28,480 
It's about time they asked us.

430
00:47:28,680 --> 00:47:31,720 
We're getting a lot of heat
from parents' groups.

431
00:47:31,880 --> 00:47:34,160 
Personally, I don't blame them.
I'm a parent.

432
00:47:34,680 --> 00:47:36,440 
All that destructive behavior.

433
00:47:37,040 --> 00:47:39,640 
He's become a role model
for our children.

434
00:47:39,880 --> 00:47:42,400 
- Now, what are we teaching them?
- You have a point.

435
00:47:42,600 --> 00:47:45,840 
If he talked things out with people
instead of firing that gun.

436
00:47:46,520 --> 00:47:49,840 
Couldn't he take a little time
to address environmental issues?

437
00:47:50,040 --> 00:47:51,080 
What was that?

438
00:47:51,240 --> 00:47:53,640 
He could speak out
on environmental issues.

439
00:47:53,840 --> 00:47:55,280 
Don't see any reason why not.

440
00:47:55,560 --> 00:47:57,080 
For all the shooting he does...

441
00:47:57,240 --> 00:48:00,520 
...l've never once seen him take the time
to do anything nice...

442
00:48:01,280 --> 00:48:05,080 
...like visit an orphanage.
- You're absolutely right.

443
00:48:05,320 --> 00:48:06,800 
Or help a cat out of a tree...

444
00:48:07,000 --> 00:48:09,680 
...or go door to door collecting
for the Red Cross...

445
00:48:09,880 --> 00:48:14,520 
...or maybe even roasting some
marshmallows with some Cub Scouts.

446
00:48:14,720 --> 00:48:20,040 
Why, Mr. Johnson, that is wonderful.
Thank you so much.

447
00:48:25,440 --> 00:48:28,440 
- It's no good. The program isn't uploading.
- He's resisting.

448
00:48:28,640 --> 00:48:29,880 
There's too much data.

449
00:48:30,040 --> 00:48:34,200 
- No, it's him. Leave him to me, Schenk.
- I can't... It's not going to work!

450
00:48:35,680 --> 00:48:37,320 
You're wasting valuable time.

451
00:48:37,760 --> 00:48:40,360 
- Don't resist us.
- Let me up.

452
00:48:41,080 --> 00:48:42,840 
I must go.

453
00:48:44,720 --> 00:48:46,000 
Go where?

454
00:48:47,160 --> 00:48:51,760 
Do what? Go dancing? Fall in love?
What is it you think you are?

455
00:48:52,360 --> 00:48:53,960 
Alex Murphy.

456
00:48:55,640 --> 00:48:56,960 
That's a delusion.

457
00:48:57,440 --> 00:49:01,160 
It's a glitch in your system.
Alex Murphy is dead.

458
00:49:01,360 --> 00:49:04,920 
Take away the metal and wires,
you're just a couple chunks on a table.

459
00:49:05,120 --> 00:49:07,160 
You're not even a corpse.

460
00:49:09,640 --> 00:49:10,960 
What are you?

461
00:49:13,480 --> 00:49:14,840 
Respond.

462
00:49:15,960 --> 00:49:19,520 
I am Officer Alex Murphy...

463
00:49:19,720 --> 00:49:21,240 
...Detroit Police Department.

464
00:49:21,480 --> 00:49:22,920 
That won't do.

465
00:49:30,040 --> 00:49:31,720 
What are you?

466
00:49:34,240 --> 00:49:38,080 
Robocop. Crime Prevention Unit.

467
00:49:38,520 --> 00:49:39,880 
OCP.

468
00:49:40,480 --> 00:49:42,720 
Better. Much better.

469
00:49:46,640 --> 00:49:47,920 
I type it. You think it.

470
00:49:48,840 --> 00:49:51,480 
You type it. I think it.

471
00:49:52,080 --> 00:49:54,920 
What a wonderful opportunity
you represent.

472
00:49:55,480 --> 00:49:57,880 
Psychotherapy, it's such a...

473
00:49:58,760 --> 00:50:03,200 
It's a slow, clumsy practice.
But with you this is so simple.

474
00:50:03,400 --> 00:50:05,120 
Direct.

475
00:50:12,440 --> 00:50:13,680 
You're lucky.

476
00:50:13,880 --> 00:50:17,720 
We can do in moments with you what
would take years with a human patient.

477
00:50:18,920 --> 00:50:21,200 
I'm really very lucky.

478
00:50:21,400 --> 00:50:25,600 
You're free. You're free from doubt.
Free from having to make painful choices.

479
00:50:27,880 --> 00:50:29,480 
I am free.

480
00:50:30,520 --> 00:50:32,160 
He's ready.

481
00:50:33,560 --> 00:50:35,360 
Uploading command program.

482
00:50:38,880 --> 00:50:42,080 
I am so glad we had this chance
to dialogue.

483
00:50:53,600 --> 00:50:56,080 
Look at you. It's like you're brand-new.

484
00:50:56,320 --> 00:50:57,680 
Thank you. Thank you.

485
00:50:57,840 --> 00:50:59,880 
You really had us worried there, Murphy.

486
00:51:00,120 --> 00:51:01,440 
I'm touched.

487
00:51:01,640 --> 00:51:03,320 
Get this guy.

488
00:51:04,160 --> 00:51:05,560 
He's touched.

489
00:51:06,560 --> 00:51:10,560 
That's enough. All of you,
back to your posts. Come on. Let's go.

490
00:51:14,320 --> 00:51:15,800 
How you feeling, Murphy?

491
00:51:16,000 --> 00:51:19,480 
I'm just fine, Warren.
Thank you for asking.

492
00:51:20,320 --> 00:51:21,880 
Let's get you downstairs.

493
00:51:22,080 --> 00:51:25,440 
I want to see what those amateurs
at OCP screwed up.

494
00:51:25,720 --> 00:51:29,000 
Pity. It's a beautiful morning.

495
00:51:29,680 --> 00:51:31,320 
Shame to waste it.

496
00:51:33,320 --> 00:51:35,480 
- Ready for duty, partner?
- You betcha.

497
00:51:35,680 --> 00:51:38,160 
- Let's go.
- Nothing I'd rather do.

498
00:51:40,320 --> 00:51:41,920 
He sounds terrific.

499
00:51:42,160 --> 00:51:43,640 
Something's wrong.

500
00:52:11,200 --> 00:52:12,240 
Harder!

501
00:52:25,080 --> 00:52:27,880 
It's Robo!
Everybody out the back door!

502
00:52:30,400 --> 00:52:32,520 
- It's locked!
- It won't open!

503
00:52:37,200 --> 00:52:39,160 
Murph, wake up, will you?

504
00:52:47,240 --> 00:52:49,040 
Good morning.

505
00:52:54,160 --> 00:52:56,120 
Come on, take him out.

506
00:53:01,400 --> 00:53:03,400 
I think we should talk.

507
00:53:07,200 --> 00:53:09,360 
What's with you, Murph?

508
00:53:16,800 --> 00:53:19,080 
- Where'd they go?
- "Where'd they go?"

509
